## Grammar

- Plurals: masc./fem.; regular and irregular patterns (e.g., חִילִים, צַעֲצוּעִים, פָּנִים)
- Basic numbers (two, three, four, many, few, all) introduced, with agreement in gender/construct form
- Possessive forms: שֶׁלִּי, שֶׁלְּךָ, שֶׁלָּהֶם, etc.
- Prepositions: בְּ, עַל, תַּחַת, בְּתוֹךְ, מִחוּץ, עִם, בְּלִי
- Opposites: יחד/בָּדָד, עם/בלִי, רבּים/מעטים, טוב/רע
- Use of teamwork and unity phrases ("together", "help", "my hand/your hand")
- Continued simple nominal/adjectival clauses
- Extensive repetition of possession ("mine", "yours", "theirs") and location
- No major new verb tense/structure innovations — most verbs remain in Qal perfect/imperfect, with participle emphasis on teamwork
- Dialogue in pronominal possession and with adjectives, to reinforce agreement

---

